She made it to the finals, with her rendition of Moloko's "Sing it back".

people.name: Malene Mortensen
people.aboutText:
Cyrill Gloor (born 23 May 1982) is a footballer from Switzerland who currently plays as defender for Old Boys Basel in the Swiss 1. Liga.
Gloor made four appearances in the Nationalliga A for FC Aarau.

people.name: Tristan Prettyman
people.aboutText: Tristan Ann Prettyman (born May 23, 1982) is an American singer-songwriter and former Roxy model from San Diego, California. She was signed to Virgin Records until 2013 and released her first major label album Twentythree on August 2, 2005, followed by her second album Hello which was released on April 15, 2008. Her third studio album, Cedar + Gold, was released on October 2, 2012.

people.name: Cas Alfonso
people.aboutText: Alfoncius Dapot Parulian Nainggolan (born 23 May 1983) also known as Cas or Cassanova Alfonso, is an Indonesian jazz singer.

people.name: Josh Pace
people.aboutText: Heidi India Range (born 23 May 1983) is an English singer and songwriter. She is best known for being a former member of the group Sugababes. Range was an original member of girl group Atomic Kitten, although she left the group two years before releasing any material.

people.name: Heidi Range
people.aboutText: Joshua Michael Pace (born May 23, 1983) is an American former professional basketball player who spent the majority of his ten-year career playing in the New Zealand National Basketball League. He also had successful stints playing college basketball for Syracuse and playing in the ABA for the Mavericks.

people.name: Alex Shelley
people.aboutText: Patrick Martin (born May 23, 1983), is an American professional wrestler, better known by the ring name Alex Shelley. He is best known for working for Total Nonstop Action Wrestling as one half of The Motor City Machine Guns with Chris Sabin. He first gained fame on the independent circuit working for Ring of Honor (ROH), as well as in Japan, for Pro Wrestling Zero1-Max.

people.name: Hugo Almeida
people.aboutText:
Hugo Miguel Pereira de Almeida (born 23 May 1984) is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays for Hannover 96 in Bundesliga as a centre forward.
After failing to establish himself at FC Porto, being loaned several times during his contract, he made a name for himself in Germany with Werder Bremen where he remained for four seasons, reaching one UEFA Cup final and scoring more than 50 official goals.
Almeida, whose international career with Portugal spanned a decade, succeeded in becoming a regular after the departures of Pauleta in 2006 and Liédson in 2010.

people.name: Sam Milby
people.aboutText: Samuel Lloyd Lacia Milby (born May 23, 1984) popularly known as Sam Milby, is a Filipino-American former reality TV contestant, actor, commercial model recording artist and businessman, of dual American and Filipino citizenship.

people.name: Kanyeria
people.aboutText:
Kanyeria (born 23 May 1985) is a Kenyan music producer, composer, sound engineer and song writer based in Nairobi, Kenya but has worked with artists and record labels in Kenya and Tanzania.
Kanyeria was born Kennedy Kanyeria in Nairobi, Kenya and lived in Ruaraka. He attended GSU Primary School and Aquinas High School and later joined the Kenya School of Monetary Studies where he attained an associate degree in Banking.

people.name: Shafiq Chitou
people.aboutText: Sekou Cissé (born 23 May 1985) is an Ivorian football striker, who currently plays for Sochaux in the Ligue 2.

people.name: Sekou Cissé
people.aboutText: Shafiq Chitou (born 23 May 1985) is a Beninese boxer. He qualified to compete in boxing at the 2012 Summer Olympics, but funding woes are a concern for him. He currently works as a house painter.

people.name: Sebastián Fernández
people.aboutText: Wim Stroetinga (born 23 May 1985 in Drachten) is a Dutch professional racing cyclist.

people.name: Wim Stroetinga
people.aboutText:
Sebastián Bruno Fernández Miglierina (born 23 May 1985) is a Uruguayan footballer who plays for Club Nacional de Football as a forward.
^ "Ficha de jugador de selección: Sebastián Fernández". Tenfield.

people.name: Ross Wallace
people.aboutText: Ross Wallace (born 23 May 1985) is a Scottish professional footballer who plays as a winger for Championship club Sheffield Wednesday.

people.name: Angela Martini
people.aboutText: Angela Martini (born Angjela Martini on 23 May 1986) is an Albanian model and beauty pageant titleholder.

people.name: Alexei Sitnikov
people.aboutText: Ruben Anton Zadkovich (born 23 May 1986) is an Australian football (soccer) player who plays for Perth Glory as a midfielder.

people.name: Ruben Zadkovich
people.aboutText: Alexei Alexandrovich Sitnikov (Russian: Алексей Александрович Ситников; born 23 May 1986) is an ice dancer. Competing for Azerbaijan with Julia Zlobina, he is the 2013 Golden Spin of Zagreb champion, 2013 Volvo Open Cup champion, 2012 Nebelhorn Trophy silver medalist, and 2013 Winter Universiade silver medalist.

people.name: Gracie Otto
people.aboutText: Windham Lawrence Rotunda (born May 23, 1987) is an American professional wrestler. He is signed to WWE, where he performs under the ring name Bray Wyatt and is the leader of The Wyatt Family. He previously wrestled for WWE as Husky Harris, most notably as a member of The Nexus.

people.name: Bray Wyatt
people.aboutText: Gracie Otto (born 23 May 1987 in Sydney) is an Australian actress, film producer, writer and director. She made her feature-length directing debut with the 2013 documentary The Last Impresario about prolific British theatre impresario and film producer Michael White. The film made its world premiere at the BFI London Film Festival in October 2013, where it was positively received by critics.

people.name: Danny de Jong
people.aboutText: Lorenzo De Silvestri (born 23 May 1988 in Rome) is an Italian footballer who plays as a defender for Serie A club Sampdoria.

people.name: Lorenzo De Silvestri
people.aboutText: Daniel "Danny" de Jong (born 23 May 1988) is a Dutch actor. A student at the Fontys Academy of Drama, he is best known for his roles on the Dutch television soap Spangas and the stage adaptation of Peter Pan, as well as numerous musicals, including Everhard in Crusade in Jeans.

people.name: Vaness del Moral
people.aboutText:
Morgan Pressel (born May 23, 1988) is an American professional golfer, currently playing on the LPGA Tour. She turned pro at age 17 and is the youngest-ever winner of a modern LPGA major championship, which vaulted her to a career-high fourth in the world rankings.
^ "Women's World Golf Rankings".

people.name: Morgan Pressel
people.aboutText: Martha Vanessa Antonio del Moral, better known by her screen name Vaness del Moral (born on May 23, 1988 in Baguio City, Benguet, Philippines), is a Filipina actress and a talent at one of the top management groups in the Philippines, the GMA Artist Center. She started her showbiz career through the interactive reality television show, StarStruck. She was eventually eliminated in Week 2.

people.name: Roope Ranta
people.aboutText:
Roope Ranta (born May 23, 1988) is a Finnish professional ice hockey forward who currently plays for SV Caldaro of the Serie A league.
^ "Colpo Caldaro, Doug Janik è un luccio" (in Italian). 2014-10-21.

people.name: Zachary Wohlman
people.aboutText:
Zachary Wohlman, known as "Kid Yamaka" (a phonetic spelling of “yarmulke,” the skullcap worn by Jews while praying), (born May 23, 1988) is an American boxer in the Welterweight division, who was an amateur and is now a professional. Wohlman, a late-comer to the sport, went from juvenile delinquency to becoming the 2010 winner of the Los Angeles Golden Gloves Tournament.
He is trained by Boxing Hall of Famer Freddie Roach, with whom he started training in 2008, and trainer Eric Brown.

people.name: Gavin Free
people.aboutText: Ezequiel Matías Schelotto (Italian pronunciation: [skeˈlɔtto]; born 23 May 1989) is an Argentinian-born Italian footballer who plays as a midfielder for the portuguese club Sporting Clube de Portugal.

people.name: Ezequiel Schelotto
people.aboutText:
Gavin David Free (born 23 May 1988) is an English actor, entertainer, producer, and filmmaker. Originally from Thame in Oxfordshire, he is best known for his work at the Austin, Texas-based production company Rooster Teeth – where he currently serves as creative director – featuring in many of their projects including the Achievement Hunter gaming division, starring in his own YouTube-based web series The Slow Mo Guys, which he created with friend Daniel Gruchy, and co-starring in the animated comedy series X-Ray and Vav.
The Slow Mo Guys features slow-motion footage of various stunts and experiments, garnering over 790 million views since it launched in 2010.

people.name: Ricardo dos Santos
people.aboutText:
Kristína Kučová (born 23 May 1990 in Bratislava) is a Slovak tennis player.
Kučová has won seven singles and four doubles on the ITF tour in her career. On 3 August 2009, she reached her best singles ranking of world number 103.

people.name: Kristína Kučová
people.aboutText: Ricardo dos Santos (23 May 1990 – 20 January 2015) was a Brazilian surfer. Dos Santos reached the quarterfinals at the 2012 Billabong Pro event in Tahiti in defeating among others Kelly Slater. At the aforementioned Tahitian tourney he was also presented with the Andy Irons award, bestowed upon the event's most determined competitor.

people.name: Raymond van Schoor
people.aboutText: Raymond van Schoor (23 May 1990 – 20 November 2015) was a Namibian cricketer. He was a right-handed batsman and occasional wicketkeeper. He was Namibia's most capped cricketer, making over 200 appearances.

people.name: Oliver Venno
people.aboutText: Oliver Venno (born 23 May 1990 in Tartu) is an Estonian volleyball player currently playing for Ziraat Bankası Ankara in Turkey.

people.name: Lena Meyer-Landrut
people.aboutText: Lena Johanna Therese Meyer-Landrut (born 23 May 1991), known professionally as Lena (pronounced [ˈleːna]), is a German singer-songwriter. She represented Germany in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010 in Oslo and won the contest with the song "Satellite". With her three entries from the German national final Unser Star für Oslo (Our Star for Oslo), Meyer-Landrut set an all-time chart record in her home country by debuting with three songs in the top five of the German singles chart.

people.name: Olesia Karmi
people.aboutText: Olesia Karmi (born 23 May 1992) is a Finnish ice dancer.

people.name: Asenate Manoa
people.aboutText:
Asenate Manoa (born 23 May 1992) is a Tuvaluan track and field athlete who represented Tuvalu at the 2008 Summer Olympics, at the 2009 World Championships & 2011 World Championships and at the 2012 Summer Olympics. Manoa represented Tuvalu in the sport of powerlifting at the Pacific Games 2015 and won a bronze medal in the 72 kg Female category.
Manoa was born on Kioa island in Fiji; Kioa was purchased by settlers from Tuvalu, who migrated from Tuvalu between 1947 and 1983.

people.name: Matthew Lintz
people.aboutText: Matthew Lintz (born May 23, 2001) is an American actor. He comes from a family of actors as his mother, Kelly Lintz, is an actress, along with his brother, Macsen, and his two older sisters, Mackenzie and Madison. He is best known for playing the role of Matty in Pixels.
